'''Bo Kristoffer Nordfeldt''' (born 23 June 1989) is a Swedish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Allsvenskan]] club [[AIK Fotboll|AIK]] and the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]].

==Club career==
===IF Brommapojkarna===
Nordfeldt began his career in [[IF Brommapojkarna]], famous for its academy. He was promoted to the first team for the season of 2006, when the team was playing in [[Superettan]]. Nordfeldt did not play any league matches that year or the following year when the team was playing for the first time in [[Allsvenskan]].{{citation needed|date=September 2018}}

In 2008, [[IF Brommapojkarna]] were back in Superettan and both goalkeepers, [[Mattias Asper]] and [[Kristoffer Björklund]], had left the club. Nordfeldt started his first year as a senior and when the season ended, the club had seen a promotion back to the Allsvenskan. He had started 29 out of 30 league matches, conceding 27 goals, and achieving 12 clean sheets.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/serier/superettan/ |title=Statistik/ligor — svenskfotboll.se |website=svenskfotboll.se |access-date=10 September 2018 |archive-date=14 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180914120620/https://www.svenskfotboll.se/serier/superettan/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> Nordfeldt signed a new contract in the beginning of 2009, keeping him at the club until 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.svenskafans.com/fotboll/artikel.asp?id=267014 |title=Silly Season 08/09 – Kristoffer Nordfeldt förlänger med BP – IF Brommapojkarna – Allsvenskan |website=svenskafans.com |url-status=dead }}</ref> As newcomers for the season of 2009, the club was seen as favourites for relegation, but finished a comfortable 12th.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/serier/allsvenskan/ |title=Tabell och resultat – Allsvenskan, herrar — svenskfotboll.se |website=svenskfotboll.se |access-date=10 September 2018 |archive-date=11 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180911002410/https://www.svenskfotboll.se/serier/allsvenskan/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> He made 21 league appearances, conceding 31 goals and keeping six clean sheets.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://svenskfotboll.se/allsvenskan/tidigare-ar/thylins-allsvenska-summering-2009/statistikligor/?scr=ml |title=Allsvensk statistik — svenskfotboll.se |website=svenskfotboll.se}}</ref>

On 2 August 2010, there were several scouts spotted at Grimsta to watch the match between [[IF Brommapojkarna]] and the league leaders [[Helsingborgs IF]]. The clubs thought to be interested in Nordfeldt were [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]], [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]], [[Hannover 96]], [[SC Heerenveen|Heerenveen]], and [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fotboll.expressen.se/allsvenskan/1.2084134/ajax-pa-plats-jagar-kristoffer-nordfeldt |title=Ajax på plats – jagar Kristoffer Nordfeldt |access-date=3 April 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111008000111/http://fotboll.expressen.se/allsvenskan/1.2084134/ajax-pa-plats-jagar-kristoffer-nordfeldt |archive-date=8 October 2011 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>

===Heerenveen===
On 6 March 2012, Nordfeldt signed a three-and-a-half-year deal at Dutch top flight club [[SC Heerenveen]]. He featured over 100 times for the Dutch side, helping them reach the Eredivisie play-offs for Europa League qualification in each of his three seasons at the club.{{citation needed|date=September 2018}}

===Swansea City===
On 23 June 2015, Nordfeldt signed for [[Premier League]] side [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]] on a three-year deal for an undisclosed fee. He was signed to compete with [[Łukasz Fabiański]] for the starting position, following the departures of goalkeepers [[Gerhard Tremmel]] and [[David Cornell]] earlier in that transfer window.<ref>{{cite web |title=Swansea City sign Swedish goalkeeper Kristoffer Nordfeldt |work=BBC Sport |date=22 June 2015 |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/33226578 |access-date=23 June 2015}}</ref> Nordfeldt made his Swansea City debut on Tuesday 25 August in their [[EFL Cup|League Cup]] match against [[York City F.C.|York City]] where he played the full 90 minutes in a 3–0 win which resulted in his first clean sheet for the club.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/33970032 |title=Swansea City 3–0 York City |work=BBC Sport |date=25 August 2015 |access-date=31 August 2017}}</ref> Nordfeldt made his Premier League debut in the last match of the [[2015–16 Premier League|season]] against [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36240334 |title=Manchester City are all but assured of a place in next season's Champions League |date=15 May 2016 |publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref>

=== AIK ===
On 9 August 2021, Nordfeldt signed a short-term contract with the Allsvenskan club [[AIK]]. The deal ran until 31 December 2021.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Officiellt: Kristoffer Nordfeldt klar för AIK - Allsvenskan - Fotbollskanalen |url=https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/artiklar/allsvenskan/officiellt-kristoffer-nordfeldt-klar-for-aik |access-date=2026-04-02 |website=www.fotbollskanalen.se |language=sv}}</ref>

He made his debut for the club on 19 August 2021 in the second round of the 2021/2022 [[Svenska Cupen|Swedish cup]] against [[Rågsveds IF]]. The match ended in a 5–0 victory for AIK, with two goals scored by [[Erik Ring (footballer)|Erik Ring]], and Nordfeldt kept a clean sheet in his first appearance for the club.<ref>{{Cite web |title=AIK Statistikdatabas |url=https://www.aikstats.se/matches.php?id=4773 |access-date=2026-04-02 |website=www.aikstats.se}}</ref> He made his Allsvenskan debut just three days later, when AIK defeated [[BK Häcken]] 2–1 at [[Nationalarenan|Friends Arena]]. His first clean sheet in the league came in the following match, a 2–0 win over [[Örebro SK]] on 28 August 2021.
[[File:Kristoffer Nordfeldt (Häcken vs AIK, 1 October 2023) (1).jpg|thumb|Nordfelt playing for AIK in 2013]]
At the end of December 2021, as his contract with the club was about to expire, Nordfeldt signed a four-year deal with AIK, keeping him at the club until 31 December 2025. In August 2025, he signed a new agreement extending his contract until 31 December 2027.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Kristoffer Nordfeldt stannar i AIK |url=https://www.aikfotboll.se//artiklar-och-nyheter/250812-kristoffer-nordfeldt-stannar-i-aik |access-date=2026-04-02 |website=AIK |language=sv}}</ref>

==International career==
Between 2008 and 2010, Nordfeldt played 16 matches for the Sweden U21-team. In the race for the 2011 U21 European Championships, Sweden played 8 matches in their qualification group and 2 in the play-offs, all with Nordfeldt in the starting lineup, with a goal difference of 17–10.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.uefa.com/under21/teams/player=250000108/index.html |title=Kristoffer Nordfeldt |archive-date=27 July 2011 |access-date=31 December 2017 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727082706/http://www.uefa.com/under21/teams/player=250000108/index.html}}</ref>

Nordfeldt made his debut for [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden]] on 22 January 2011 in a friendly match against [[South Africa national development football team|South Africa Development team]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://svenskfotboll.se/arkiv/landslag/2011/01/herr-sydafrika-sverige1/ |title=Herr: 1–1 i Nelspruit — svenskfotboll.se |website=svenskfotboll.se|access-date=19 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111216004837/http://svenskfotboll.se/arkiv/landslag/2011/01/herr-sydafrika-sverige1/|archive-date=16 December 2011|url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref>
[[File:Russia-Sweden 2015 (8).jpg|thumb|Nordfelt with Sweden in 2015]]
In May 2018, he was named in the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden 23 man squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb |title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad - 23-man & preliminary lists & when will they be announced? - Goal.com }}</ref>

Nordfeldt was included in Sweden 26-man squad for [[UEFA Euro 2020]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Sweden Euro 2020 squad: Full team profile |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/sweden-euro-2020-squad-the-complete-line-up-for-marchs-internationals |website=[[FourFourTwo]] |date=14 June 2021 |access-date=14 June 2021 |ref=euro2020squad}}</ref>

Nordfeldt delivered two notable performances for Sweden in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA second round|2026 World Cup playoff]], playing a key role in both matches as the team secured qualification.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/sweden-qualify-world-cup-2026 |access-date=2026-04-02 |website=www.fifa.com}}</ref>

In the playoff semifinal against [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]] on 26 March 2026, played in [[Spain]] (relocated due to the [[Russo-Ukrainian war (2022–present)|war in Ukraine]]), Sweden won 3–1. Nordfeldt started in goal and made a strong impact in what was his first competitive international appearance in several years. He assisted [[Viktor Gyökeres]] for one of the goals. Sweden controlled much of the game, and although they conceded late, Nordfeldt’s overall performance was considered both composed and decisive.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Ames |first=Nick |date=2026-03-26 |title=Viktor Gyökeres hits hat-trick as Sweden and Graham Potter see off Ukraine |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2026/mar/26/ukraine-sweden-world-cup-qualifying-playoff-semi-final-match-report |access-date=2026-04-02 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref>

In the playoff final against [[Poland national football team|Poland]] on 31 March 2026, played in [[Stockholm]], Sweden won 3–2 to secure a place in the 2026 World Cup.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Wilson |first=Jonathan |date=2026-04-01 |title=Graham Potter and Sweden revel in second chances to seize World Cup place |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2026/apr/01/graham-potter-sweden-second-chances-world-cup |access-date=2026-04-02 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> Nordfeldt once again started and played the full match.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sundberg |first=Tor |date=2026-03-30 |title=Potter meddelar – Nordfeldt står igen: "Närmare hundra" |url=https://fotbolldirekt.se/vm-fotboll/potter-meddelar-nordfeldt-star-igen-narmare-hundra/ |access-date=2026-04-02 |website=FotbollDirekt |language=sv-SE}}</ref>

These two matches show how Nordfeldt stepped in and went from being a backup option to a crucial figure in Sweden’s successful playoff run.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Orre |first=Foto: Pontus |date=2026-04-01 |title=Hyllas av Potter: ”En otrolig kille” |url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/a/PddzPX |access-date=2026-04-02 |website=www.aftonbladet.se |language=sv}}</ref>

